text: Marvin Richard James Humes (born 18 March 1985) is a British singer, songwriter, actor, DJ, and televison presenter. He is best known for being a member of the boy band JLS, alongside runners up from the X Factor (series 5) in the United States from 2006 to 2013. Since spring 2013, he runs the Capital Weekender beginning with The weekend lives on Capital!. He also owned the official big top 40.
